The Resident Electoral Commissioner (REC) in Niger State, Prof. Sam Egwu, says the commission is ready for the general elections rescheduled due to logistic challenges. Speaking during an inspection of materials alongside political party representatives and security agencies at the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) office in Minna, Prof. Egwu said all materials were intact and ready to be deployed for the Saturday exercise. Prof Egwu said the anomaly leading to the rescheduling of the general elections was a temporary setback which is being addressed. He called on Nigerians to have faith in the ability of the commission to conduct free and fair polls. The commissioner commended the CBN, security agencies and the commission’s staffers for working hard towards securing the materials after the botched exercise. INEC sets for presidential, NASS polls in Niger, says materials intact No ballot papers missing – Niger REC 2,167,788 voter’s cards collected in Niger, says REC